    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="306"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 351.117/73</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Sharp</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1302. Your 1406, March 4. Foreign Office replies that in France, Louis Levy is
                    French, being born abroad of a French father; that as such he is subject in
                    France to the obligations of military service; and that under these conditions
                    his request does not seem susceptible of favorable action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
